  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process Technician",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Purpose of the Position</strong></u></p>\n<p>Reporting to the Shift Supervisor, the Process Technician's primary responsiblity is to ensure the smooth operation of his/her assigned Process Unit, be it in either the Field or DCS Panel Operation.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p>\n<p><u>DCS Operation</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform starts up and shuts down according to Standard Operating Procedures, Work Instructions or Checklists.</li>\n  <li>Monitor and control process variables via DCS (towers, reactors, driers, compressors, etc) to maintain quality &amp; plant in steady &amp; efficient condition.</li>\n  <li>Respond to process alarms, process upsets or abnormal process conditions according to established practices and procedures in order to begin or cease production as advised by Supervisor or Engineers.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoots equipment and/or process problems in order to identify needed corrections or improvements.</li>\n  <li>Initiate and perform Safety bypass with approval from Supervisor.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u>Field Operation</u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Performs equipment line-ups and operate towers, reactors, driers, compressors, pumps, etc according to established practices and procedures.</li>\n  <li>Responds to upsets or abnormal process conditions according to instructions from Supervisor or Panelman.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoots equipment and/or process problems in order to identify needed corrections or improvements.</li>\n  <li>Collect process samples from assigned sampling points in a safe manner.</li>\n  <li>Equipment Inspection Tours according to checklist.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>NITEC in Chemical Process Technology /Diploma in Chemical Engineering or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Min. 1-2 years Operational experience with demonstrable exposure to Process Plant Operations and site-based activity or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Experience in Safety Awareness programs or involvement in Safety Committees will be an added advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
